Hi {!Contact.FirstName},
I hope all is well at Akin, Gump, Strauss, Hauer & Feld, LLP. I work for Compliance Week and wanted to let you know that we are going to cover the topic of Anti-Trust Issues at our upcoming annual conference in May in DC.
As a sponsor to the event, Akin, Gump, Strauss, Hauer & Feld LLP can lead this session and help customize the session topic.
The Compliance Week 2017 Annual Conference will be held May 22 to 24, 2017, at the Mayflower Hotel, Washington DC. The conference designed to help senior compliance executives from global public companies understand how to build and manage their compliance and risk programs more effectively. There will be feature keynote presentations from key government regulators such as the SEC and DOJ. The sponsors are given two speaking slots and are able to interact and network with an audience of 500 senior legal, financial, risk and compliance executives. The cost of sponsorship is $55,000. http://conference.complianceweek.com/cw-2016/home-cw2016.aspx. Attached to this email you will find:
Word doc - full list of sponsorship opportunities; PDF outline of presenting sponsorship benefits; Excel doc - registration list from the 2016 event.
As a sponsor, you would be able to lead/moderate TWO sessions. The cost and benefits of sponsorship:
Full Presenting Sponsorship- Cost: $55,000
-Leadership of a large room panel session (approx. 100 execs)
-Leadership of small room boardroom style conversation (approx. 15 execs)
-Exhibit booth
-Attendee List
-Media exposure and branding
-Participation in welcome reception
-Access to event management team to plan a dinner
-Participation in a seated lunch, ability to pick who sits at your lunch table
-Opportunity to distribute promotional materials to attendees
-Full page advertisement in brochure
-Four conferences passes, plus passes for all speakers
Please let me know if you have questions or would like to chat on the phone. Thanks for your consideration.
Julie
